    {
        "content": "<p>You are telling Lean to unify the expected type <code>self.beq a b = true → self.beq b a = true</code> with the term <code>Eq.symm : ?a = ?b → ?b = ?a</code>. So instead of using the default value for <code>beq</code>, it infers that <code>beq</code> needs to be <code>fun a b =&gt; true</code>. This is then reflected in the goal generated by <code>by</code>.</p>\n<p>So this is Lean being maybe a bit too smart :)</p>",
        "id": 537777219,
        "sender_full_name": "Jovan Gerbscheid",
        "timestamp": 1757034253
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can avoid this surprising behaviour by using <code>by</code> for all your proofs:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bld</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PartialOrd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">compare</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">none</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">compare_eq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">eq_symm'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Eq</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">symm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- error message is here</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
